  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Covid-19 response led by communities in North-East Haiti</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">SJM through this project is exploring how community mobilisers could work with CBOs to identify prioirity needs and mobilise resources to meet their needs. PALC volunteers from communities will be trained to support CBOs in the process. CBOs will develop micro-projects as part of the SCLR process. At least  5 micro-grants will be funded through the process. The project should target both gender but encourage more women lead group.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&quot;These following results will be achieved by the end of the project period:
1.	Communities affected by COVID-19 in Ouanaminthe and Capotille will have increased access to responses that are relevant and appropriate.                                                                                                                                               

2.	Community groups capacity on leading appropriate and relevant responses increased in Ouanaminthe and Capotille.
3.	The target area communities have increased skills and capacities to identify their needs and develop and implement micro-projects that address their felt needs

4.	Evidence of SCLR as a model of community-led emergency response will be enhanced</narrative>
  </description>
